
	<sn><md>## Comparing Changes in Git{.text-center}

When working with Git, you often need to compare file changes at different stages of development. The `git diff` command is the primary tool for this purpose. It allows you to inspect changes in your working directory, staging area, and even against previous commits.

This article covers how to use `git diff` to:

1. View changes between the **working directory and the staging area**.
2. View changes between the **staging area and the last commit**.
